    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\non [NormalNvim](https://github.com/NormalNvim/NormalNvim) we ship shortcut buttons on the winbar.\r\n![screenshot_2024-03-21_04-31-19_736066824](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/3357792/31c1e919-cbb1-40ff-958d-f1c53699c833)\r\n\r\nBecause on neovim the winbar is per split by default, opening a split will duplicate the controls.\r\n![screenshot_2024-03-21_04-31-09_250427733](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/3357792/f89d6f4f-99f1-42f6-bab7-0d2ffc280306)\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIt would be great having a option for having a single winbar for the visible area, instead of default per split.",
